
[1]noon

   NOON, n. [ said to be from naw, that is up or ultimate, that limits,
   also nine. I has been supposed that the ninth hour, among the Romans,
   was the time of eating the chief meal; this hour was three o'clock,
   P.M. In Danish, none is an afternooning, a collation.]

   1. The middle of the day; the time when the sun is in the meridian;
   twelve o'clock.

   2. Dryden used the word for midnight. "At the noon of night."

                            NOON, a. Meridional.

   How of the noon bell.
